WEBVTT



00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.350
Yeah

00:00:11.456 --> 00:00:17.824
I'm Derek Walker, I'm the pastor of the Oxford Bible Church and today I want to introduce you to my book.

00:00:17.536 --> 00:00:19.968
Called growing up spiritually.

00:00:20.096 --> 00:00:21.600
God wants us all.

00:00:21.344 --> 00:00:23.328
To grow up spiritually.

00:00:23.200 --> 00:00:27.072
In Peter, it says that as newborn babes,

00:00:26.944 --> 00:00:30.176
We should desire the pure milk

00:00:29.952 --> 00:00:33.504
Of God's word that we may grow thereby.

00:00:33.600 --> 00:00:42.304
Whether we are spiritual babies, we've just been born again, or or whether we're further along in our spiritual growth, this book,

00:00:41.984 --> 00:00:49.056
Will give you the keys and the understanding you need to continue to grow spiritually.

00:00:48.800 --> 00:00:56.992
which is God's desire for you. God wants everyone to be saved and to come to the knowledge of the truth and to grow strong.

00:00:56.672 --> 00:00:58.176
As believers.

00:00:59.392 --> 00:01:07.840
Do you want to grow up spiritually and become strong in spirit, in faith and in love, or do you just want to stay a spiritual babe?

00:01:08.224 --> 00:01:11.456
God wants us to be spiritual giants, not wimps.

00:01:11.072 --> 00:01:14.432
And he's provided all we need for our growth in God.

00:01:16.064 --> 00:01:23.392
This book will reveal God's will and ways to gain a dynamic spiritual life and to promote

00:01:23.520 --> 00:01:25.824
A consistent growth in grace.

00:01:26.208 --> 00:01:30.976
So discover the keys that will activate and perpetuate your growth.

00:01:31.872 --> 00:01:33.216
In this brook,

00:01:32.960 --> 00:01:37.280
The first chapter looks at the different stages of growth.

00:01:37.088 --> 00:01:40.064
From babyhood to full maturity.

00:01:39.744 --> 00:01:46.400
And then we look at rebound techniques that are essential so that our growth isn't quickly stopped.

00:01:46.016 --> 00:01:53.280
How to rebound from sin, how to rebound from setbacks, how to rebound from success, how to handle success.

00:01:53.344 --> 00:01:59.296
Then we talk about walking in love, which is absolutely the key to spiritual maturity.

00:01:59.264 --> 00:02:04.416
We talk about how the Bible describes the spiritual food that we need to take in.

00:02:04.672 --> 00:02:13.088
And then we look at the foundation for all our growth that we need to build on, which is our baptism into Christ and all that that means.

00:02:13.600 --> 00:02:19.424
We talk about the tongue because the Bible puts great emphasis on how we use our tongues.

00:02:19.552 --> 00:02:22.880
And we go into the revelation of our words.

00:02:22.592 --> 00:02:29.344
When we talk about how we are to move into ministry so that we're not just taking in but we're giving out.

00:02:29.792 --> 00:02:33.824
And then we talk about the different means of grace, the channels of grace.

00:02:34.368 --> 00:02:36.192
Prayer, fellowship,

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:37.888
Communion.

00:02:37.920 --> 00:02:40.032
the Word of God.

00:02:39.840 --> 00:02:43.104
And through these channels God imparts the grace of goodness.

00:02:42.880 --> 00:02:46.912
His grace to us that we may grow. so I recommend this book to you.

00:02:46.784 --> 00:02:49.856
For your spiritual nourishment and growth.
